Package: bootupd
Version: {{ VER }}
Architecture: amd64
Maintainer: Gabriel Guillou guillou.gabriel@gmail.com
Homepage: https://github.com/DaemonCores/debian-bootc
Section: admin
Priority: required
Pre-Depends: grub-efi-amd64, grub-efi-amd64-signed, shim-signed
Depends: {{ DEPS }}, util-linux
Description: cross-distribution EFI bootloader update manager
 Manages updates to EFI bootloader components (shim, GRUB) independently
 of the ostree-managed root filesystem. In a bootc system the EFI System
 Partition lies outside the ostree tree and cannot be updated through the
 normal container image update path; bootupd bridges this gap by tracking
 and updating EFI binaries as a separate, managed component.
 .
 Compiled from upstream Fedora CoreOS sources and pre-configured to manage
 the shim and GRUB EFI binaries provided by the grub-efi-amd64-signed
 and shim-signed packages in this repository.
